7:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1916:\"<p><strong>MySearchTermsPresenter</strong> is a WP plugin which will store the incoming searchterms and automatically integrate it to the article. If a visitor has found an article on your website using a search engine the searchterm will be collected and saved.</p>\n<p>A lot of WP administrators are using <a title=\"mysearchtermspresenter - display incoming search terms\" href=\"http://exells.com/shop/seo-wordpress-plugins/mysearchtermspresenter/\">MySearchTermsPresenter</a> and are <strong>really impressed of the impact</strong>! All sites which have installed the plugin are experiencing a <strong>boost in SERP</strong> (search engine result pages). MySearchTermsPresenter was introduced about a year ago. Since then a lot has changed and the plugin has been <strong>enhanced and optimized</strong>.</p>\n<p>A few days ago MySearchTermsPresenter was released in the Version 4.10. Take a look to the <strong>new features</strong>:</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-478\"></span><strong>Black-List:</strong> The admin is able to define a list of forbidden words. Every incoming searchterm which contains one of the blacklisted words will not be saved.</p>\n<p><strong>Ajax Delete:</strong> Integrated searchterms can be deleted directly from the article site. This is realized with the Ajax technology. The delete will be processed in the background and no reload of the site will be necessary.</p>\n<p><strong>More Search Engines supported:</strong> 4 new search engines are supported now. With Ask, MSN, Baidu and AOL MySearchTermsPresenter is able to collect incoming searchterms from more than 7 search engines.</p>\n<p><strong>Searchterms Counter:</strong> Every incoming searchterms will be counted and in the plugin backend you can see how often a searchterm was used.</p>\n<p><strong>Searchterms on pages and articles:</strong> Th